      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WOODSTOCK (10) is still learning but building nicely and should be ready to peak fourth-up after being beaten a long neck last time at Oakbank. Gets in well with the claim and should prove very tough to stop. TREVIDI (7) returns for the Stokes camp and looks to have come on a treat during the break. Has been readied with three hitouts, pushed out nicely at his most recent. Draws well and can give this a big shake. NOW EAST (5) was poised to strike when resuming at Oakbank but just lacked a fitness edge. Is sure to have come on from that and gets in well with the 2kg claim. Expecting sharp improvement. BJARNE (2) finds the maiden win elusive but has some ratings littered through his form that can measure up here. Expect him to take a sit off the early speed and look to reel them in.",
